    About

    Description

    Paul Jackson Pollock was an American painter. A major figure in the abstract expressionist movement, Pollock was widely noticed for his "drip technique" of pouring or splashing liquid household paint onto a horizontal surface, enabling him to view and paint his canvases from all angles. Wikipedia
    Born: January 28, 1912, Cody, WY
    Died: August 11, 1956 (age 44 years), Springs, NY
    Periods: Abstract expressionism, Modern art, Action painting
    Influenced by: Pablo Picasso, Joan Mir, Max Ernst, Thomas Hart Benton, Jiddu Krishnamurti, Mark Tobey, John D. Graham
    Spouse: Lee Krasner (m. 19451956)
